How the Tool Is Exposed to the Model

The tool schema and the tool output are included in the recovery-agent prompt. The LLM receives the structured output and uses it to choose one of four modes:

SCHEDULE_MODE
RECOVERY_MODE
TRIAGE_MODE
WARNING_MODE

The tool does not directly produce the final plan. It provides structured context so the LLM can make a more informed decision.

MCP Honesty Note

This draft uses a custom MCP-style tool implemented inside the project codebase. It defines the tool schema, exposes the structured output to the model, and displays the tool trace in the UI.

It is not currently a separate external MCP server.
